parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the front suspension components, including the cross member, control arms, and wheel bearings, can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving
the steering wheel pulls to one side
the vehicle makes a loud noise
the front suspension components show signs of rust or corrosion
the vehicle loses control while braking or turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the brake lines can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake light comes on
the vehicle loses braking power
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Notification of Recall and Warranty
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to notify owners of recalls and warranties can lead to delayed or missed repairs, resulting in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Owners are not informed of recalls or warranties
owners are not notified of safety issues
owners are not provided with necessary repairs or replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical components to malfunction, such as brakes, horn, and lights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuses and breakers keep popping/blowing
loss of brake light functionality
inability to use the horn
failure of dashboard lighting
door locks
and emergency flashers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle suddenly stalls while driving
inability to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to lose track of their speed, which can lead to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer needle stuck
speedometer reads incorrectly
speedometer stops working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Vehicle won't start
anti-theft system light on dashboard pops on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause various safety-critical components to malfunction, such as the odometer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Odometer doesn't light up properly
inability to see mileage on the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents or traffic hazards.
symptoms: One or both headlights fail
poor electrical engineering/manufacturing of the headlight system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
occupants sustain injuries or fatalities that could have been prevented or minimized by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause unexpected and potentially hazardous situations, such as sudden stops or loss of control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without any apparent reason
such as when the vehicle is stationary or not involved in a crash.
